A '''child disability allowance''' is a payment made by the [[government of New Zealand]] to the parent or [[legal guardian|guardian]] of a seriously disabled child who incurs regular costs by having a [[disability]]. It is not [[means-tested benefit|means-tested]].  The child must have been assessed as needing constant care and attention for at least 12 months because of a serious disability.<ref>{{cite web|title=Child Disability Allowance|url=http://www.workandincome.govt.nz/individuals/a-z-benefits/child-disability-allowance.html|website=Work and Income|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref>

