{{Infobox body of water |name = Funnsjøen |native_name = |native_name_lang = |other_name = |image = |caption = |image_bathymetry = |alt_bathymetry = |caption_bathymetry = |pushpin_map = Trøndelag#Norway |pushpin_label_position = bottom |pushpin_map_caption = Location of the lake |coordinates = {{coord|63.5253|11.7118|region:NO_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} |location = [[Meråker]], [[Trøndelag]] |type = |inflow = |outflow = Funna |catchment = [[Stjørdalselva]] |basin_countries = [[Norway]] |date-built = |date-flooded = |length = {{convert|8|km}} |width = {{convert|3|km}} |area = {{convert|7.99|km2|abbr=on}} |depth = |max-depth = |volume = {{convert|64,000,000|m3|yd3|abbr=on}} |residence_time = |shore = {{convert|25|km}} |elevation = {{convert|442|m}} |frozen = |islands = |cities = |reference = [[Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate|NVE]] }}
'''Funnsjøen''' is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Meråker]] in [[Trøndelag]] county, [[Norway]]. The {{convert|8|km2|adj=on}} lake flows into the Funna river, a part of the [[Stjørdalselva]] river system. The lake has a [[hydroelectricity|hydropower]] [[dam]] at the southern end of the lake. There is about {{convert|64,000,000|m3|yd3}} of water stored behind the dame in the lake.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snl.no/Funna|title=Funna|editor-first=Knut A.|editor-last=Rosvold|accessdate=2018-03-24|date=2011-12-15|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|publisher=[[Kunnskapsforlaget]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
The lake is located about {{convert|6.5|km}} north of the municipal center of [[Midtbygda, Trøndelag|Midtbygda]]. The lake [[Feren]] lies north of the lake and the lake [[Fjergen]] lies southeast of the lake.
